                            <comment id="421880" author="JIRAUSER18604" created="Mon, 22 Jul 2024 23:17:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The new test will fail like this without the fix&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;== sanity test 56xh: lfs migration --non-block copy ====== 23:15:12 (1721690112)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;dd: warning: partial read (115 bytes); suggest iflag=fullblock&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;0+256 records in&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;0+256 records out&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;18972 bytes (19 kB, 19 KiB) copied, 0.0502337 s, 378 kB/s&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;lfs migrate: can&apos;t create composite layout from file /mnt/lustre/d56xh.sanity.src: Numerical result out of range&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;sanity test_56xh: @@@@@@ FAIL: migrate remote dir error /mnt/lustre/d56xh.sanity.src /mnt/lustre/d56xh.sanity.dest/f56xh.sanity.mgrt&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160; Trace dump:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160; = /usr/lib64/lustre/tests/test-framework.sh:6755:error()&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160; = /usr/lib64/lustre/tests/sanity.sh:8028:test_56xh()&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160; = /usr/lib64/lustre/tests/test-framework.sh:7075:run_one()&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160; = /usr/lib64/lustre/tests/test-framework.sh:7125:run_one_logged()&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160; = /usr/lib64/lustre/tests/test-framework.sh:6945:run_test()&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160; = /usr/lib64/lustre/tests/sanity.sh:8030:main()&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Dumping lctl log to /tmp/test_logs/2024-07-22/231507/sanity.test_56xh.*.1721690112.log&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Dumping logs only on local client.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;CMD: test1-single-node lctl set_param -n osc.*.pinger_recov=1&#160; &#160; 2&amp;gt;/dev/null&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;FAIL 56xh (0s)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="421871" author="adilger" created="Mon, 22 Jul 2024 21:18:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This ticket would be much more useful if it included the output from those commands, instead of leaving it as an exercise to the reader to determine what is wrong...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m assuming that the last migrate does not pick the right OST?  That said, I can&apos;t predict whether this is a bug because the migrated file stays on the same OST or because it is moving to a new OST...  Both of those outcomes might be considered &quot;correct&quot; depending on your expectations. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
